I'm enjoying what I've played (campaign aside because EA execs rushed it and its just not good) but a few things are nagging me: - Maps feel too small or cramped at times. Im forced to have to restart the game to fix it, although this doesnt always work. Map designs are a joke also, who ever thought of placing a large mountain ranges right next to HQ anti air defences and spawns, surely has never played previous battlefield games. It just allows the enemy team to use the mountain range to spawn camp vehicles without being targeted. People are toxic and will abuse anything they can for a hollow win, did they assume players would spawn camp? On second thoughts, after reading my review back for spelling mistakes, i realise its pretty negative. Ill come back and change it when things improve

<<The Legendary Return of Battlefield ‚Äî Now in a ‚ÄúReal Man‚Äôs Shooter‚Äù Wrapper>> No pink ponies or mysterious fairies here ‚Äî just testosterone and bullets. I love Battlefield, but this sixth installment has a bunch of serious screw-ups. Until they fix them, the game is basically unplayable. Vehicles For the love of God ‚Äî on most maps with vehicles, the vehicles don‚Äôt even spawn properly. Even worse: on some maps, one team gets them and the other doesn‚Äôt. For example, on ‚ÄúSiege of Cairo‚Äù, PAX gets both an AA gun and a helicopter, while NATO only gets the AA. And what the hell is that AA gun supposed to do without a chopper? Balance The f***ing M4A1 ‚Äî I swear, I‚Äôm so done with it. I can understand players under level 20 using it ‚Äî they don‚Äôt have much unlocked yet. But when you see idiots at level 50+ still running around with that thing, it‚Äôs just pathetic. Overall, out of all the guns, there are like 2‚Äì3 that completely destroy the balance, and the rest are garbage by comparison. Even BF4 had ‚ÄúOP guns,‚Äù but this is over the line. They seriously need to reduce recoil and increase precision and nerf those overpowered ones (for example m4a1 take 20 dmg), and maybe then things will start to feel fair again. Maps During the beta, the maps ran perfectly on my RTX 5070 ‚Äî a stable 200 FPS on max settings. Now, after release, the new maps still run 180‚Äì200 FPS on ultra, but the old beta ones drop to 80‚Äì100 FPS. No clue what happened ‚Äî nothing major seems to have changed. What‚Äôs even weirder: large maps run fine, but small ones tank the FPS. Drivers are updated, settings on ultra ‚Äî no idea what‚Äôs going on. Vehicles (More Detail) The attack helicopter is actually well-balanced ‚Äî good upgrade options, customizable loadouts. Jets are fine too, though they could use some updates (I get it, early release and all ‚Äî hopefully soon). As for the APC ‚Äî damn, the ammo runs out way too fast and takes forever to refill. No proper machine gun to deal with infantry, so your gunner just can‚Äôt keep up. The tank‚Ä¶ man, it‚Äôs just too weak. The heavy MG is useless, the shells do barely any damage or splash, and the anti-missile system takes an eternity to recharge. Either buff it or add another tank variant, because I‚Äôm sick of getting blown up by a single dude with an RPG. Right now, vehicles are just way too weak ‚Äî everything needs a buff except the attack heli and jet. Map Balance I swear, whoever designed the Breakthrough mode capture points must‚Äôve been an idiot. Either the defense is way too weak or the attackers are overpowered. Basically, defense gets screwed. It‚Äôs especially ‚Äúfun‚Äù when vehicles should spawn but don‚Äôt because of a bug. That‚Äôs when you just want to burn the damn server to the ground. Verdict Battlefield 6 could‚Äôve been an absolute top-tier game ‚Äî it‚Äôs got the potential, the atmosphere, the classic Battlefield spirit ‚Äî but all of that is buried under a pile of awful balance issues. If DICE doesn‚Äôt fix this, the game‚Äôs doomed, and no amount of testosterone will save it. But if they pull it together ‚Äî it could be one hell of a shooter, truly worthy of the Battlefield name. Guys I really love BF. I wish BF4 would just be updated and I would have a blast. But now I need to whine a little and Vince Zampella will try to do better: 0/10

It's really a good game. I've tried a similar kind of this game and I think I'm in favor of the gameplay. BF6 is the first BF game I've ever tried and it really amazes me. With all these dust and collapse and other something(like a very dazzling light), it's really difficult to see enemy and you will die suddenly because your enemy has seen you. Besides, the sniper in this game is really powerful, especially when you are playing the ‚Äúbreak‚Äù mode, and you are in the attack camp. You can see lots of flashlight far in front of you and you can do nothing about it. As for the EXP system, actually I think it's bad but it's OK.
